# NOTE: GoogleService-Info.plist + google-services.json are intentionally
# NOT gitignored. Google's own docs confirm those config files are not
# secrets — the API key in them is the *public* Firebase Web API key
# and is restricted by bundle ID + Firebase Security Rules. Keeping them
# in the repo simplifies onboarding new devs and CI. The actual secrets
# (Firebase Admin service-account JSON, Strava client SECRET) stay on the
# server side only — see apps/api/.env.example.

